This paper deals with the use of Wi-Fi signals to predict mobility modes, which falls under the category of networked and mobile systems (cs.NI). The paper also utilizes machine learning techniques such as deep neural networks and decision trees, which are commonly used in the field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with signal processing and feature extraction, which are important topics in the field of signal processing (cs.SI). The paper also deals with privacy and security concerns related to Wi-Fi signals, which falls under the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR). Finally, the paper deals with image processing techniques such as feature extraction, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV).
